# Stack (job-application-tracker)

**Authoritative versions:** See `package.json`. Do not assume or invent versions.

## Runtime

| Layer        | Technology        | Notes |
|-------------|--------------------|-------|
| Framework   | Next.js 16 (App Router) | `next` in package.json |
| UI library  | React 19           | `react`, `react-dom` |
| Auth        | Clerk              | `@clerk/nextjs` |
| Styling     | Tailwind CSS v4    | `tailwindcss`, `@tailwindcss/postcss` |
| Components  | shadcn/ui, Radix   | `radix-ui`, `@radix-ui/react-slot`, etc. |
| State       | Zustand (client)   | `zustand` |
| Server state| TanStack Query     | `@tanstack/react-query` |
| Forms       | React Hook Form    | `react-hook-form` |
| Validation  | Zod                | `zod` (v4 in this project) |
| DB          | Drizzle ORM        | `drizzle-orm`, `drizzle-kit` |
| DB host     | Neon (PostgreSQL)  | `@neondatabase/serverless` |
| PDF         | jspdf              | `jspdf` |
| AI          | OpenAI             | `openai` (env: `OPENAI_API_KEY`) |
| Email parse | mammoth, googleapis | For parsing / Gmail |
| Toasts      | Sonner             | `sonner` |

## Dev / tooling

- TypeScript 5
- ESLint 9, eslint-config-next 16
- Tailwind v4 (canonical classes: see `tailwind.mdc`)

## What we do not use

- Prisma (we use Drizzle)
- NextAuth (we use Clerk)
- Redux (we use Zustand + TanStack Query)

When adding dependencies or referring to APIs, check `package.json` and official docs for the exact package and version.
